60.7	Black-Scholes	Black–Scholes	As above, the Black–Scholes equation is a partial differential equation, which describes the price of the option over time. The key idea behind the equation is that one can perfectly hedge the option by buying and selling the underlying asset in just the right way and consequently “eliminate risk". This hedge, in turn, implies that there is only one right price for the option, as returned by the Black–Scholes formula given in the next section. The Equation:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Stockpricesimulation.jpg/220px-Stockpricesimulation.jpg
